modules.description: Provides functions to load, validate, and execute eBPF programs, including setting up registers and handling memory mappings. Works with byte sequences, eBPF instructions, and program contexts. Used to embed low-level network filtering and tracing logic directly into user-space applications.

Loads and executes BPF or ELF programs, compiling them to machine code for efficient execution. Accepts string-based BPF or ELF input and returns a handle for running and releasing resources. Executes programs with specific input strings, returning integer results.
